{"id":28737,"date":"2024-02-02T15:37:18","date_gmt":"2021-12-02T10:07:18","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=28737"},"modified":"2022-10-19T17:57:43","modified_gmt":"2022-10-19T12:27:43","slug":"7-bathroom-design-hacks-for-small-spaces","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bathroom-interiors\/7-bathroom-design-hacks-for-small-spaces\/","title":{"rendered":"Bathroom Designs For Small Spaces | These Handy Design Hacks Help You Do More With Less"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>Make your small shower planet appear bigger and spacious with these savvy design hacks<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A good, comfortable bathroom is bliss! After a long day of work, you can just take a hot bath and feel relieved instantly. But a bathroom design can totally affect your time in your bathroom. After all, a cramped bathroom with a disorganised design won&#8217;t let you feel calm like the way a luxurious and spacious bathroom can! But it doesn&#8217;t mean that only a large-sized bathroom can heal your stress. Smart bathroom designs for small spaces can achieve the same results.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>At <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/\">DesignCafe<\/a>, we provide modular design solutions that can make a small space feel airy. Thus for your small bathrooms, we got you some innovative design solutions to redefine your bathroom. So, unravel the following amazing small bathroom designs to let you use every corner of your shower planet.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">1.&nbsp; Choose The Right Colour For Your Bathroom Designs For Small Spaces<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In interior design, colour is one of the most important aesthetics. It can influence your feeling towards a space. That&#8217;s why while designing spaces, the choice of colours becomes crucial. This is particularly useful for small spaces as the wrong colour may make them look cramped. So, for your small space bathroom, go with colours that are light and airy. Think of light pink, beige, white and cream. Avoid dark colours like black, blue and deep brown as they can make the bathroom look smaller and jam-packed. If you don&#8217;t want to experiment a lot, go with white. White tiles in a small spaced bathroom can make it appear clean and spacious.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152243\/bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-with-the-right-colour.jpg\" alt=\"Bathroom design for small spaces with colours hack\" class=\"wp-image-28740\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152243\/bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-with-the-right-colour.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152243\/bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-with-the-right-colour-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152243\/bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-with-the-right-colour-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152243\/bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-with-the-right-colour-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A white marble bathroom design with minimal design elements is a classic<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">2. Our Modular Storage Solutions Are Perfect For Indian Bathroom Designs For Small Spaces<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Your bathroom space can be home to things like the washing machine, toiletries and hair dryers. And these items require an organised setup to not mess up your shower space. Thus, at Design Cafe, we go for modular storage units to keep small bathrooms clutter-free and organised. For this Indian bathroom design for small spaces, we have used a tall storage unit that encloses the washing machine, towels and other utilities. When not in use, you can simply shut the unit to keep things out of sight.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152314\/storage-solution-for-indian-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces.jpg\" alt=\"Indian bathroom designs for small spaces with a space-saving storage unit\" class=\"wp-image-28745\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152314\/storage-solution-for-indian-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152314\/storage-solution-for-indian-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152314\/storage-solution-for-indian-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152314\/storage-solution-for-indian-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Furnish a small bathroom with a space-saving storage unit for a clutter-free look<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Design your bathroom with our end to end home interior solutions\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/06115036\/design-your-bathroom-with-our-end-to-end-home-interior-solutions-scaled.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">3. Go With A Glass Partition To Separate The Shower Area In Modern Bathroom Designs For Small Spaces<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In your small spaced bathroom, separate your shower area from the rest of the space with a transparent glass partition. The clear glass partition doesn\u2019t obstruct the space visually and makes it appear big and seamless. With an opaque partition, the bathroom will look more closed and cramped. Therefore go for clear glass partitions. You can also use frosted glass. However, with a see-through partition, the space will look wider and more accessible.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152302\/modern-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-with-glass-partition.jpg\" alt=\"Modern bathroom design hack for small spaces with glass partition\" class=\"wp-image-28743\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152302\/modern-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-with-glass-partition.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152302\/modern-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-with-glass-partition-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152302\/modern-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-with-glass-partition-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152302\/modern-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-with-glass-partition-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A clear glass partition separates the shower area without making the bathroom more cramped<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">4. Modern Bathroom Designs For Small Spaces Make The Most Of Under Sink Area<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We know that a bathroom needs a lot of storage options. Especially if you are someone (like us) who is particular about using different bathroom products. Modern bathroom designs for small spaces utilise the under-sink area to create the perfect vanity storage option. As you can see, we have designed a handleless drawer unit under the sink. This utilises the unused space and adds a handy storage option. Next to the sink, you can place your washing machine to further utilise the area. If you need more storage, go for a wall-mounted vertical shelf unit above the sink area.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152237\/bathroom-design-ideas-for-small-spaces-with-clutter-free-storage.jpg\" alt=\"Bathroom design ideas for small spaces with vanity storage options\" class=\"wp-image-28739\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152237\/bathroom-design-ideas-for-small-spaces-with-clutter-free-storage.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152237\/bathroom-design-ideas-for-small-spaces-with-clutter-free-storage-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152237\/bathroom-design-ideas-for-small-spaces-with-clutter-free-storage-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152237\/bathroom-design-ideas-for-small-spaces-with-clutter-free-storage-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A small spaced bathroom with a clutter-free, handleless drawer unit under the sink<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, Read About <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/under-sink-storage-ideas\/\">Under Sink Storage Ideas<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">5. Use Floating Vanity Unit Ideas To Create Modern Bathroom Designs For Small Spaces<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Another great way to make your small bathroom look spacious is by switching to a floating vanity unit. The wall-mounted floating vanity unit will take less space and let you have an open sink design. The floating unit will also utilise the vertical space of your bathroom. This will let you enjoy more floor space. These floating vanity units are great for minimal and sleek bathroom designs. Hence, it is ideal for urban Indian apartments with less spacious rooms.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152249\/floating-vanity-unit-create-modern-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces.jpg\" alt=\"Modern bathroom design for small space with floating vanity unit\" class=\"wp-image-28741\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152249\/floating-vanity-unit-create-modern-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152249\/floating-vanity-unit-create-modern-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152249\/floating-vanity-unit-create-modern-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152249\/floating-vanity-unit-create-modern-bathroom-designs-for-small-spaces-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A cosy bathroom design with a space-saving floating vanity unit<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, Read About <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bathroom-interiors\/bathroom-vanity-designs\/\">Bathroom Vanity Designs<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">6. Add A Seamless Floor-To-Ceiling Visual Design Element In Your Small Bathroom&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A floor-to-ceiling tile design plays a visual trick and makes the space appear larger. In bathroom designs for small spaces, a mosaic tile paper that connects the floor and ceiling area of the shower section creates a seamless design continuity. Thus when you enter the bathroom, you will draw your eyes towards the ceiling. This makes the bathroom space appear bigger. The accent tile paperwork also adds dimension to the bathroom design. With such an element, you can also break the monotony of white bathroom designs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152255\/great-bathroom-design-for-small-space-with-accent-tiles.jpg\" alt=\"Floor-to-ceiling tile bathroom design for small space\" class=\"wp-image-28742\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152255\/great-bathroom-design-for-small-space-with-accent-tiles.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152255\/great-bathroom-design-for-small-space-with-accent-tiles-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152255\/great-bathroom-design-for-small-space-with-accent-tiles-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152255\/great-bathroom-design-for-small-space-with-accent-tiles-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A white bathroom design with an accent floor-to-ceiling tile design<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">7. Add Large Mirrors And Glossy Tiles To Make Your Small Bathroom Look Spacious<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Mirrors always do the trick! It has always been known that mirrors and reflective surfaces can make a small space look bigger. Therefore, if you have a small bathroom, include large mirrors in the design. You can also make the space appear big by adding glossy tile work. The tiles will act as reflecting surfaces in your bathroom design. Go for beige or white glossy tiles to make your bathroom appear spacious and airy. Additionally, you can add a space-saving vanity unit design and a glass partition to make the room appear clutter-free.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152308\/simple-bathroom-design-for-small-space-with-large-mirrors.jpg\" alt=\"Simple bathroom design hack for small space with a large mirror and glossy tiles\" class=\"wp-image-28744\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152308\/simple-bathroom-design-for-small-space-with-large-mirrors.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152308\/simple-bathroom-design-for-small-space-with-large-mirrors-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152308\/simple-bathroom-design-for-small-space-with-large-mirrors-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/02152308\/simple-bathroom-design-for-small-space-with-large-mirrors-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A modern bathroom design with a large mirror and glossy tiles<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Although we spend only some time of the day in our bathrooms, they are the places where we relax and rejuvenate. Hence, designing the bathroom as per our needs is a crucial part of home interiors. These are some expert-recommended tips on Indian bathroom designs for small spaces. So, if you are looking for further expert consultation for your <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/bedroom-design\/\">bathroom interiors<\/a>, reach out to us. We will create the best restful bathroom space, even in the smallest homes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Explore, More About <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bathroom-interiors\/bathroom-mirror-design-ideas\/\">Bathroom Mirror Design Ideas<\/a><\/p>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 